│ i32 %add57.i, %div.i4`.                                                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ The other operand to this `add` is `%div.i4`, which is `sdiv i32 1, 0`. This is undefined behavior and evaluates to a `poison` constant. When an operation has a    │
│ `poison` operand, the result is also `poison`. It's likely that some earlier transformation or analysis within the `indvars` pass constant-folds the `add`          │
│ instruction to `poison` because one of its operands is `poison`.                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
