│ THOUGHT                                                                                                                                                             │
│ I am presented with the same LLVM crash issue again. My previous analysis correctly identified the root cause: the `indvars` pass was attempting to use a pointer   │
│ to an instruction that had been deleted. This happens because an operation involving `poison` (`sdiv i32 1, 0`) gets constant-folded, leading to the deletion of    │
│ dependent instructions. The pass, however, still holds a stale pointer to one of these deleted instructions.                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ The proven solution is to add a check in `llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SimplifyIndVar.cpp`. Specifically, after getting a pointer to an instruction from a use list,   │
│ we must verify that the instruction has not been deleted by checking if it still has a parent basic block.                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ I will re-apply the exact same successful patch. The command combines the file modification using `sed` and the verification using `submit-patch` with `&&` to      │
│ ensure they run in the same environment.                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                             │
│ sed -i "/Instruction \*NarrowInc = cast<Instruction>(U.getUser());/a \    if (!NarrowInc->getParent())\n      continue;"                                            │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/SimplifyIndVar.cpp && submit-patch                                                                                                        │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                 │
